				content: "‘Mercy gives its judgement an honourable welcome’; literally, ‘mercy exalts judgement’. This appears to be the sense of the Latin text, which is perhaps due to an error of copying. The sense of the Greek is, ‘Mercy can boast over (its) judgement’."
